    <h3><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Legal Responsibilities</h3>
    <div class="info-card"><i class="fas fa-file-signature"></i><h4>Biosecurity Act 2019 (Tasmania)</h4>
    <p>Declared weeds <strong>must</strong> be controlled on your land. It is an offence to propagate, spread, or sell declared weeds. Environmental weeds are not always declared under legislation, but may still require control under land management responsibilities, local regulations, or conservation agreements.</p></div>
    
    <div class="info-card"><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i><h4>Record Keeping</h4><p>For commercial operators: Keep records of herbicide usage (product, rate, date, location, weather conditions) for at least 3 years. Required for chemical user permits.</p></div>

    <div class="trap-card"><i class="fas fa-skull"></i> <strong>Critical:</strong> Never spray herbicides near waterways without checking the label's aquatic buffer zone. Some chemicals cannot be used within 20m-100m of water. Civil penalties apply.</div>
</div>
